# Observability Rules (可观测性)

Every user action, error, and performance-critical operation MUST be instrumented.

## 1. Event Analytics (AnalyticsManager)

```swift
// ✅ GOOD - track every user action with typed event
AnalyticsManager.shared.track(.captureStarted(method: "ReplayKit"))
AnalyticsManager.shared.track(.exportSaved(format: "png"))
AnalyticsManager.shared.track(.settingsChanged(key: "autoScroll", value: "true"))

// ✅ GOOD - track failures in EVERY catch block
} catch {
    AnalyticsManager.shared.track(.captureFailed(error: error.localizedDescription))
}

// ❌ BAD - silent catch
} catch { errorMessage = error.localizedDescription }  // no tracking
```

### Required events for new features

- `*Started` / `*Completed` / `*Failed` for any async operation
- `settingsChanged(key:value:)` for every toggle/picker in Settings
- `screenshotDeleted` / `screenshotOpened` for user data actions
- `error(domain:code:)` for non-feature errors (memory, config, etc.)

## 2. Error Handling (SCError + ErrorPresenter)

```swift
// ✅ GOOD - ALL errors go through SCError
throw SCError.capture(.permissionDenied)
throw SCError.network(.offline)

// ✅ GOOD - present to user via ErrorPresenter (auto-tracks analytics)
ErrorPresenter.shared.present(error)

// ✅ GOOD - map package errors to SCError at boundary
} catch {
    let msg = (error as? SCError)?.userMessage ?? String(localized: "error.capture.recording")
    ErrorPresenter.shared.present(error)
}

// ❌ BAD - local errorMessage without ErrorPresenter or analytics
self.errorMessage = error.localizedDescription  // user sees raw English, no tracking
```

### Rules

- Never show `error.localizedDescription` to users — use `SCError.userMessage`
- Every `catch` block must either `ErrorPresenter.shared.present()` or `AnalyticsManager.track()`
- Map package-level errors (`CaptureServiceError`, `StoreError`) to `SCError` at app boundary

## 3. Performance (PerformanceMonitor)

```swift
// ✅ GOOD - wrap hot paths with signposts
let sid = PerformanceMonitor.beginCapture()
// ... capture work ...
PerformanceMonitor.endCapture(sid, frames: count)

let sid = PerformanceMonitor.beginExport(format: "png")
// ... export work ...
PerformanceMonitor.endExport(sid)

// ✅ GOOD - memory check runs periodically (every 60s in ScrollCapApp)
PerformanceMonitor.reportMemoryUsage()
```

### Rules

- Capture, stitch, and export MUST have begin/end signposts
- Memory is checked every 60s; >500MB triggers an analytics event
- Use `PerformanceMonitor.measure("name") { }` for ad-hoc measurements

## 4. Crash Reporting (CrashReporter)

- Installed in `ScrollCapApp.init()` (before UI loads)
- Signal handler is async-signal-safe (only `write(2)` + `_exit`)
- NSException handler captures full stack trace
- Previous crashes detected on next launch via sentinel file

## 5. Network (APIClient)

```swift
// ✅ GOOD - all HTTP goes through APIClient
try await APIClient.shared.request(Response.self, url: endpoint)

// ❌ BAD - raw URLSession
let (data, _) = try await URLSession.shared.data(from: url)
```

### Rules

- NEVER use raw `URLSession` — always `APIClient.shared`
- `NetworkMonitor.shared.isConnected` checked before every request
- Exponential backoff retry for 408/429/5xx
- Request/response logged with method, URL, status code, and duration

## 6. Logging (SCLogger)

```swift
// ✅ GOOD - use typed logger categories
SCLogger.capture.started("region: full")
SCLogger.capture.completed("frames: 42", duration: 3.2)
SCLogger.capture.failed("startCapture", error: error)

// ❌ BAD - print() or unstructured logging
print("capture started")
```

## Checklist for new features

- [ ] User action tracked with `AnalyticsManager.shared.track()`
- [ ] Every `catch` has either `ErrorPresenter.present()` or `track()`
- [ ] Async operations have begin/end signposts if >100ms expected
- [ ] Errors mapped to `SCError` at package boundary
- [ ] Uses `SCLogger` category, not `print()`
- [ ] No raw `URLSession` — uses `APIClient`
